headline: D.R. Horton (DHI) Margin Miss Challenges Bullish Valuation Narrative
summary: D.R. Horton (DHI) reported revenue growth projected at 5.5% per year, which trails the broader US market’s 10.3% pace. EPS is forecast to rise 8.4% annually, again behind the US average of 15.7%, with the latest results showing a year-over-year decline and net profit margin narrowing from 12.9% to 10.5%. Despite solid profit quality and continued growth expectations, investors are taking a closer look at the company's elevated price-to-earnings ratio and softer momentum after recent negative...
